# Coding Standards

- Use strict TypeScript types; avoid `any` unless justified.
- Validate all external input with Zod on the server boundary.
- Keep modules small and single-responsibility.
- Isolate third-party integrations behind adapter interfaces.
- Avoid hardcoded public strings in UI; use translation keys.
- Never commit secrets or provider credentials.
